This directory contains a component that fetches the current weather from
https://openweathermap.org/ and generates a report that is used to display the
information via a menu_view component.

Configuration
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

! <config update_interval="30" api_key="xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx">
!   <location id="2935022" query="Dresden,DE" units="metric"/>
!   <vfs>
!     <dir name="dev">
!       <log/> <null/>
!       <inline name="rtc">2018-09-10 00:00</inline>
!       <inline name="random">01234567890123456789</inline>
!     </dir>
!     <dir name="socket"> <lxip dhcp="yes"/> </dir>
!   </vfs>
!   <libc stdout="/dev/null" stderr="/dev/null" rtc="/dev/rtc" socket="/socket"/>
! </config>

This exemplary configuration will poll OWM every 30 minutes using the specified
API key and will ask for the current weather in Dresden. The location can be
specified either by the ID, which can be obtain on the OWM website, or by name.
If both attributes are specified the 'id' attribute takes precedence. The
temperature is requested in Celsius. Valid values for the 'units' attribute are
'imperial' (Fahrenheit) and 'metric' (Celsius). If it is omitted, the
temperature will be requested in Kelvin by default.

Report
~~~~~~

The generated Report looks as follows

! <dialog>
!   <frame>
!     <vbox>
!       <label text="Dresden"/>
!       <hbox>
!         <label text="broken clouds"/>
!         <label text="11"/>
!         <label text="°C"/>
!       </hbox>
!     </vbox>
!   </frame>
! </dialog>

while the LOG message looks like this:

! Current: 'Dresden' 11°C (broken clouds)
